sw0657841Dot1XAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuth.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

sw0657841Dot1XAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuth.name: sw0657841Dot1XAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticated
sw0657841Dot1XAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuth.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to DISCONNECTED, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message being received from the Supplicant.

sw0657841Dot1XBackendResponses.name: sw0657841Dot1XBackendResponses
sw0657841Dot1XBackendResponses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an initial Access-Request packet to the Authentication server (i.e., executes sendRespToServer on entry to the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authenticator attempted communication with the Authentication Server.

sw0657841Dot1XBackendAccessChallenges.name: sw0657841Dot1XBackendAccessChallenges
sw0657841Dot1XBackendAccessChallenges.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an initial Access-Challenge packet from the Authentication server (i.e., aReq becomes TRUE, causing exit from the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authentication Server has communication with the Authenticator.

sw0657841Dot1XBackendOtherRequestsToSupp.name: sw0657841Dot1XBackendOtherRequestsToSupplicant
sw0657841Dot1XBackendOtherRequestsToSupp.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an EAP-Request packet (other than Indentity, Notification, Faluire or Success message) to the Supplicant (i.e., executes txReq on entry to the REQUEST state). Indicates that Authenticator chose an EAP-method.

sw0657841Dot1XBackendAuthSuccesses.name: sw0657841Dot1XBackendAuthSuccesses
sw0657841Dot1XBackendAuthSuccesses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Success message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aSuccess becomes TRUE, causing a transitions from RESPONSE to SUCCESS). Indicates that the Supplicant has successfully authenticated to the Authentication Server.

sw0657841Dot1XBackendAuthFails.name: sw0657841Dot1XBackendAuthFails
sw0657841Dot1XBackendAuthFails.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Failure message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aFail becomes TRUE, causing a transitions from RESPONSE to FAIL). Indicates that the Supplicant has not authenticated to the Authentication Server.
